PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F307A1780567570
OL,3,CPolice watchdog urges public to 'stop
OL,4,Cspeculating' about Henry Nowak's murder
OL,6,FStarmer said there is no justification
OL,7,Ffor more violence and disorder
OL,8,Ffollowing the murder of Mr Nowak.
OL,10,FHe criticised Nigel Farage after the
OL,11,FReform UK leader asserted that the UK
OL,12,Fhas "two-tier policing" and that
OL,13,Fofficers are told to treat different
OL,14,Fethnic groups differently.
OL,16,FFarage faced repeated calls from other
OL,17,FMPs to "condemn the violence".
OL,19,FStarmer said Reform UK leader's
OL,20,F"appeal for rage" was "unforgivable".
OL,26,@tD@EOUtD@WO]|D@AOU|D@QO]|D@WOU|D@dO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G4/12
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,308,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30705
SC,0005
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F307A1780567570
OL,3,CPolice watchdog urges public to 'stop
OL,4,Cspeculating' about Henry Nowak's murder
OL,6,F"The grieving family have asked us not
OL,7,Fto respond in the way that the leader
OL,8,Fof Reform has responded," Starmer said.
OL,10,F"They've asked us not to. They have
OL,11,Flost their son in the most appalling
OL,12,Fcircumstance. They make a simple plea
OL,13,Fto us as human beings to please not
OL,14,Fexploit that. That is their plea to
OL,15,Fus."
OL,17,FStarmer praised the responses from
OL,18,Fopposition leaders, Kemi Badenoch and
OL,19,FEd Davey, thanking them for their
OL,20,F"approach and tone" in relation to the
OL,21,Fcase.
OL,26,@nD@AOU
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G5/12
